2311  /**
2312   * Efficiently moves many courses around while maintaining
2313   * sortorder in order.
2314   *
2315   * @param array $courseids is an array of course ids
2316   * @param int $categoryid
2317   * @return bool success
2318   */
2319  function move_courses($courseids, $categoryid) {
2320      global $DB;
2321  
2322      if (empty($courseids)) {
2323          // Nothing to do.
2324          return false;
2325      }
2326  
2327      if (!$category = $DB->get_record('course_categories', array('id' => $categoryid))) {
2328          return false;
2329      }
2330  
2331      $courseids = array_reverse($courseids);
2332      $newparent = context_coursecat::instance($category->id);
2333      $i = 1;
2334  
2335      list($where, $params) = $DB->get_in_or_equal($courseids);
2336      $dbcourses = $DB->get_records_select('course', 'id ' . $where, $params, '', 'id, category, shortname, fullname');
2337      foreach ($dbcourses as $dbcourse) {
2338          $course = new stdClass();
2339          $course->id = $dbcourse->id;
2340          $course->category  = $category->id;
2341          $course->sortorder = $category->sortorder + MAX_COURSES_IN_CATEGORY - $i++;
2342          if ($category->visible == 0) {
2343              // Hide the course when moving into hidden category, do not update the visibleold flag - we want to get
2344              // to previous state if somebody unhides the category.
2345              $course->visible = 0;
2346          }
2347  
2348          $DB->update_record('course', $course);
2349  
2350          // Update context, so it can be passed to event.
2351          $context = context_course::instance($course->id);
2352          $context->update_moved($newparent);
2353  
2354          // Trigger a course updated event.
2355          $event = \core\event\course_updated::create(array(
2356              'objectid' => $course->id,
2357              'context' => context_course::instance($course->id),
2358              'other' => array('shortname' => $dbcourse->shortname,
2359                               'fullname' => $dbcourse->fullname)
2360          ));
2361          $event->set_legacy_logdata(array($course->id, 'course', 'move', 'edit.php?id=' . $course->id, $course->id));
2362          $event->trigger();
2363      }
2364      fix_course_sortorder();
2365      cache_helper::purge_by_event('changesincourse');
2366  
2367      return true;
2368  }

2411  /**
2412   * Can the current user delete this course?
2413   * Course creators have exception,
2414   * 1 day after the creation they can sill delete the course.
2415   * @param int $courseid
2416   * @return boolean
2417   */
2418  function can_delete_course($courseid) {
2419      global $USER;
2420  
2421      $context = context_course::instance($courseid);
2422  
2423      if (has_capability('moodle/course:delete', $context)) {
2424          return true;
2425      }
2426  
2427      // hack: now try to find out if creator created this course recently (1 day)
2428      if (!has_capability('moodle/course:create', $context)) {
2429          return false;
2430      }
2431  
2432      $since = time() - 60*60*24;
2433      $course = get_course($courseid);
2434  
2435      if ($course->timecreated < $since) {
2436          return false; // Return if the course was not created in last 24 hours.
2437      }
2438  
2439      $logmanger = get_log_manager();
2440      $readers = $logmanger->get_readers('\core\log\sql_reader');
2441      $reader = reset($readers);
2442  
2443      if (empty($reader)) {
2444          return false; // No log reader found.
2445      }
2446  
2447      // A proper reader.
2448      $select = "userid = :userid AND courseid = :courseid AND eventname = :eventname AND timecreated > :since";
2449      $params = array('userid' => $USER->id, 'since' => $since, 'courseid' => $course->id, 'eventname' => '\core\event\course_created');
2450  
2451      return (bool)$reader->get_events_select_count($select, $params);
2452  }

2454  /**
2455   * Save the Your name for 'Some role' strings.
2456   *
2457   * @param integer $courseid the id of this course.
2458   * @param array $data the data that came from the course settings form.
2459   */
2460  function save_local_role_names($courseid, $data) {
2461      global $DB;
2462      $context = context_course::instance($courseid);
2463  
2464      foreach ($data as $fieldname => $value) {
2465          if (strpos($fieldname, 'role_') !== 0) {
2466              continue;
2467          }
2468          list($ignored, $roleid) = explode('_', $fieldname);
2469  
2470          // make up our mind whether we want to delete, update or insert
2471          if (!$value) {
2472              $DB->delete_records('role_names', array('contextid' => $context->id, 'roleid' => $roleid));
2473  
2474          } else if ($rolename = $DB->get_record('role_names', array('contextid' => $context->id, 'roleid' => $roleid))) {
2475              $rolename->name = $value;
2476              $DB->update_record('role_names', $rolename);
2477  
2478          } else {
2479              $rolename = new stdClass;
2480              $rolename->contextid = $context->id;
2481              $rolename->roleid = $roleid;
2482              $rolename->name = $value;
2483              $DB->insert_record('role_names', $rolename);
2484          }
2485      }
2486  }

2488  /**
2489   * Returns options to use in course overviewfiles filemanager
2490   *
2491   * @param null|stdClass|course_in_list|int $course either object that has 'id' property or just the course id;
2492   *     may be empty if course does not exist yet (course create form)
2493   * @return array|null array of options such as maxfiles, maxbytes, accepted_types, etc.
2494   *     or null if overviewfiles are disabled
2495   */
2496  function course_overviewfiles_options($course) {
2497      global $CFG;
2498      if (empty($CFG->courseoverviewfileslimit)) {
2499          return null;
2500      }
2501      $accepted_types = preg_split('/\s*,\s*/', trim($CFG->courseoverviewfilesext), -1, PREG_SPLIT_NO_EMPTY);
2502      if (in_array('*', $accepted_types) || empty($accepted_types)) {
2503          $accepted_types = '*';
2504      } else {
2505          // Since config for $CFG->courseoverviewfilesext is a text box, human factor must be considered.
2506          // Make sure extensions are prefixed with dot unless they are valid typegroups
2507          foreach ($accepted_types as $i => $type) {
2508              if (substr($type, 0, 1) !== '.') {
2509                  require_once($CFG->libdir. '/filelib.php');
2510                  if (!count(file_get_typegroup('extension', $type))) {
2511                      // It does not start with dot and is not a valid typegroup, this is most likely extension.
2512                      $accepted_types[$i] = '.'. $type;
2513                      $corrected = true;
2514                  }
2515              }
2516          }
2517          if (!empty($corrected)) {
2518              set_config('courseoverviewfilesext', join(',', $accepted_types));
2519          }
2520      }
2521      $options = array(
2522          'maxfiles' => $CFG->courseoverviewfileslimit,
2523          'maxbytes' => $CFG->maxbytes,
2524          'subdirs' => 0,
2525          'accepted_types' => $accepted_types
2526      );
2527      if (!empty($course->id)) {
2528          $options['context'] = context_course::instance($course->id);
2529      } else if (is_int($course) && $course > 0) {
2530          $options['context'] = context_course::instance($course);
2531      }
2532      return $options;
2533  }

2535  /**
2536   * Create a course and either return a $course object
2537   *
2538   * Please note this functions does not verify any access control,
2539   * the calling code is responsible for all validation (usually it is the form definition).
2540   *
2541   * @param array $editoroptions course description editor options
2542   * @param object $data  - all the data needed for an entry in the 'course' table
2543   * @return object new course instance
2544   */
2545  function create_course($data, $editoroptions = NULL) {
2546      global $DB;
2547  
2548      //check the categoryid - must be given for all new courses
2549      $category = $DB->get_record('course_categories', array('id'=>$data->category), '*', MUST_EXIST);
2550  
2551      // Check if the shortname already exists.
2552      if (!empty($data->shortname)) {
2553          if ($DB->record_exists('course', array('shortname' => $data->shortname))) {
2554              throw new moodle_exception('shortnametaken', '', '', $data->shortname);
2555          }
2556      }
2557  
2558      // Check if the idnumber already exists.
2559      if (!empty($data->idnumber)) {
2560          if ($DB->record_exists('course', array('idnumber' => $data->idnumber))) {
2561              throw new moodle_exception('courseidnumbertaken', '', '', $data->idnumber);
2562          }
2563      }
2564  
2565      // Check if timecreated is given.
2566      $data->timecreated  = !empty($data->timecreated) ? $data->timecreated : time();
2567      $data->timemodified = $data->timecreated;
2568  
2569      // place at beginning of any category
2570      $data->sortorder = 0;
2571  
2572      if ($editoroptions) {
2573          // summary text is updated later, we need context to store the files first
2574          $data->summary = '';
2575          $data->summary_format = FORMAT_HTML;
2576      }
2577  
2578      if (!isset($data->visible)) {
2579          // data not from form, add missing visibility info
2580          $data->visible = $category->visible;
2581      }
2582      $data->visibleold = $data->visible;
2583  
2584      $newcourseid = $DB->insert_record('course', $data);
2585      $context = context_course::instance($newcourseid, MUST_EXIST);
2586  
2587      if ($editoroptions) {
2588          // Save the files used in the summary editor and store
2589          $data = file_postupdate_standard_editor($data, 'summary', $editoroptions, $context, 'course', 'summary', 0);
2590          $DB->set_field('course', 'summary', $data->summary, array('id'=>$newcourseid));
2591          $DB->set_field('course', 'summaryformat', $data->summary_format, array('id'=>$newcourseid));
2592      }
2593      if ($overviewfilesoptions = course_overviewfiles_options($newcourseid)) {
2594          // Save the course overviewfiles
2595          $data = file_postupdate_standard_filemanager($data, 'overviewfiles', $overviewfilesoptions, $context, 'course', 'overviewfiles', 0);
2596      }
2597  
2598      // update course format options
2599      course_get_format($newcourseid)->update_course_format_options($data);
2600  
2601      $course = course_get_format($newcourseid)->get_course();
2602  
2603      // Setup the blocks
2604      blocks_add_default_course_blocks($course);
2605  
2606      // Create a default section.
2607      course_create_sections_if_missing($course, 0);
2608  
2609      fix_course_sortorder();
2610      // purge appropriate caches in case fix_course_sortorder() did not change anything
2611      cache_helper::purge_by_event('changesincourse');
2612  
2613      // new context created - better mark it as dirty
2614      $context->mark_dirty();
2615  
2616      // Save any custom role names.
2617      save_local_role_names($course->id, (array)$data);
2618  
2619      // set up enrolments
2620      enrol_course_updated(true, $course, $data);
2621  
2622      // Trigger a course created event.
2623      $event = \core\event\course_created::create(array(
2624          'objectid' => $course->id,
2625          'context' => context_course::instance($course->id),
2626          'other' => array('shortname' => $course->shortname,
2627                           'fullname' => $course->fullname)
2628      ));
2629      $event->trigger();
2630  
2631      return $course;
2632  }

2634  /**
2635   * Update a course.
2636   *
2637   * Please note this functions does not verify any access control,
2638   * the calling code is responsible for all validation (usually it is the form definition).
2639   *
2640   * @param object $data  - all the data needed for an entry in the 'course' table
2641   * @param array $editoroptions course description editor options
2642   * @return void
2643   */
2644  function update_course($data, $editoroptions = NULL) {
2645      global $DB;
2646  
2647      $data->timemodified = time();
2648  
2649      $oldcourse = course_get_format($data->id)->get_course();
2650      $context   = context_course::instance($oldcourse->id);
2651  
2652      if ($editoroptions) {
2653          $data = file_postupdate_standard_editor($data, 'summary', $editoroptions, $context, 'course', 'summary', 0);
2654      }
2655      if ($overviewfilesoptions = course_overviewfiles_options($data->id)) {
2656          $data = file_postupdate_standard_filemanager($data, 'overviewfiles', $overviewfilesoptions, $context, 'course', 'overviewfiles', 0);
2657      }
2658  
2659      // Check we don't have a duplicate shortname.
2660      if (!empty($data->shortname) && $oldcourse->shortname != $data->shortname) {
2661          if ($DB->record_exists_sql('SELECT id from {course} WHERE shortname = ? AND id <> ?', array($data->shortname, $data->id))) {
2662              throw new moodle_exception('shortnametaken', '', '', $data->shortname);
2663          }
2664      }
2665  
2666      // Check we don't have a duplicate idnumber.
2667      if (!empty($data->idnumber) && $oldcourse->idnumber != $data->idnumber) {
2668          if ($DB->record_exists_sql('SELECT id from {course} WHERE idnumber = ? AND id <> ?', array($data->idnumber, $data->id))) {
2669              throw new moodle_exception('courseidnumbertaken', '', '', $data->idnumber);
2670          }
2671      }
2672  
2673      if (!isset($data->category) or empty($data->category)) {
2674          // prevent nulls and 0 in category field
2675          unset($data->category);
2676      }
2677      $changesincoursecat = $movecat = (isset($data->category) and $oldcourse->category != $data->category);
2678  
2679      if (!isset($data->visible)) {
2680          // data not from form, add missing visibility info
2681          $data->visible = $oldcourse->visible;
2682      }
2683  
2684      if ($data->visible != $oldcourse->visible) {
2685          // reset the visibleold flag when manually hiding/unhiding course
2686          $data->visibleold = $data->visible;
2687          $changesincoursecat = true;
2688      } else {
2689          if ($movecat) {
2690              $newcategory = $DB->get_record('course_categories', array('id'=>$data->category));
2691              if (empty($newcategory->visible)) {
2692                  // make sure when moving into hidden category the course is hidden automatically
2693                  $data->visible = 0;
2694              }
2695          }
2696      }
2697  
2698      // Update with the new data
2699      $DB->update_record('course', $data);
2700      // make sure the modinfo cache is reset
2701      rebuild_course_cache($data->id);
2702  
2703      // update course format options with full course data
2704      course_get_format($data->id)->update_course_format_options($data, $oldcourse);
2705  
2706      $course = $DB->get_record('course', array('id'=>$data->id));
2707  
2708      if ($movecat) {
2709          $newparent = context_coursecat::instance($course->category);
2710          $context->update_moved($newparent);
2711      }
2712      $fixcoursesortorder = $movecat || (isset($data->sortorder) && ($oldcourse->sortorder != $data->sortorder));
2713      if ($fixcoursesortorder) {
2714          fix_course_sortorder();
2715      }
2716  
2717      // purge appropriate caches in case fix_course_sortorder() did not change anything
2718      cache_helper::purge_by_event('changesincourse');
2719      if ($changesincoursecat) {
2720          cache_helper::purge_by_event('changesincoursecat');
2721      }
2722  
2723      // Test for and remove blocks which aren't appropriate anymore
2724      blocks_remove_inappropriate($course);
2725  
2726      // Save any custom role names.
2727      save_local_role_names($course->id, $data);
2728  
2729      // update enrol settings
2730      enrol_course_updated(false, $course, $data);
2731  
2732      // Trigger a course updated event.
2733      $event = \core\event\course_updated::create(array(
2734          'objectid' => $course->id,
2735          'context' => context_course::instance($course->id),
2736          'other' => array('shortname' => $course->shortname,
2737                           'fullname' => $course->fullname)
2738      ));
2739  
2740      $event->set_legacy_logdata(array($course->id, 'course', 'update', 'edit.php?id=' . $course->id, $course->id));
2741      $event->trigger();
2742  
2743      if ($oldcourse->format !== $course->format) {
2744          // Remove all options stored for the previous format
2745          // We assume that new course format migrated everything it needed watching trigger
2746          // 'course_updated' and in method format_XXX::update_course_format_options()
2747          $DB->delete_records('course_format_options',
2748                  array('courseid' => $course->id, 'format' => $oldcourse->format));
2749      }
2750  }

2752  /**
2753   * Average number of participants
2754   * @return integer
2755   */
2756  function average_number_of_participants() {
2757      global $DB, $SITE;
2758  
2759      //count total of enrolments for visible course (except front page)
2760      $sql = 'SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (
2761          SELECT DISTINCT ue.userid, e.courseid
2762          FROM {user_enrolments} ue, {enrol} e, {course} c
2763          WHERE ue.enrolid = e.id
2764              AND e.courseid <> :siteid
2765              AND c.id = e.courseid
2766              AND c.visible = 1) total';
2767      $params = array('siteid' => $SITE->id);
2768      $enrolmenttotal = $DB->count_records_sql($sql, $params);
2769  
2770  
2771      //count total of visible courses (minus front page)
2772      $coursetotal = $DB->count_records('course', array('visible' => 1));
2773      $coursetotal = $coursetotal - 1 ;
2774  
2775      //average of enrolment
2776      if (empty($coursetotal)) {
2777          $participantaverage = 0;
2778      } else {
2779          $participantaverage = $enrolmenttotal / $coursetotal;
2780      }
2781  
2782      return $participantaverage;
2783  }

2785  /**
2786   * Average number of course modules
2787   * @return integer
2788   */
2789  function average_number_of_courses_modules() {
2790      global $DB, $SITE;
2791  
2792      //count total of visible course module (except front page)
2793      $sql = 'SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (
2794          SELECT cm.course, cm.module
2795          FROM {course} c, {course_modules} cm
2796          WHERE c.id = cm.course
2797              AND c.id <> :siteid
2798              AND cm.visible = 1
2799              AND c.visible = 1) total';
2800      $params = array('siteid' => $SITE->id);
2801      $moduletotal = $DB->count_records_sql($sql, $params);
2802  
2803  
2804      //count total of visible courses (minus front page)
2805      $coursetotal = $DB->count_records('course', array('visible' => 1));
2806      $coursetotal = $coursetotal - 1 ;
2807  
2808      //average of course module
2809      if (empty($coursetotal)) {
2810          $coursemoduleaverage = 0;
2811      } else {
2812          $coursemoduleaverage = $moduletotal / $coursetotal;
2813      }
2814  
2815      return $coursemoduleaverage;
2816  }

2999      /**
3000       * Checks that the shortname used by the course does not conflict with any other
3001       * courses that exist
3002       *
3003       * @param string|null $shortnamemark The string to append to the requests shortname
3004       *                     should a conflict be found
3005       * @return bool true is there is a conflict, false otherwise
3006       */
3007      public function check_shortname_collision($shortnamemark = '[*]') {
3008          global $DB;
3009  
3010          if ($this->properties->collision !== null) {
3011              return $this->properties->collision;
3012          }
3013  
3014          if (empty($this->properties->shortname)) {
3015              debugging('Attempting to check a course request shortname before it has been set', DEBUG_DEVELOPER);
3016              $this->properties->collision = false;
3017          } else if ($DB->record_exists('course', array('shortname' => $this->properties->shortname))) {
3018              if (!empty($shortnamemark)) {
3019                  $this->properties->shortname .= ' '.$shortnamemark;
3020              }
3021              $this->properties->collision = true;
3022          } else {
3023              $this->properties->collision = false;
3024          }
3025          return $this->properties->collision;
3026      }

3028      /**
3029       * Returns the category where this course request should be created
3030       *
3031       * Note that we don't check here that user has a capability to view
3032       * hidden categories if he has capabilities 'moodle/site:approvecourse' and
3033       * 'moodle/course:changecategory'
3034       *
3035       * @return coursecat
3036       */
3037      public function get_category() {
3038          global $CFG;
3039          require_once($CFG->libdir.'/coursecatlib.php');
3040          // If the category is not set, if the current user does not have the rights to change the category, or if the
3041          // category does not exist, we set the default category to the course to be approved.
3042          // The system level is used because the capability moodle/site:approvecourse is based on a system level.
3043          if (empty($this->properties->category) || !has_capability('moodle/course:changecategory', context_system::instance()) ||
3044                  (!$category = coursecat::get($this->properties->category, IGNORE_MISSING, true))) {
3045              $category = coursecat::get($CFG->defaultrequestcategory, IGNORE_MISSING, true);
3046          }

3053      /**
3054       * This function approves the request turning it into a course
3055       *
3056       * This function converts the course request into a course, at the same time
3057       * transferring any files used in the summary to the new course and then removing
3058       * the course request and the files associated with it.
3059       *
3060       * @return int The id of the course that was created from this request
3061       */
3062      public function approve() {
3063          global $CFG, $DB, $USER;
3064  
3065          $user = $DB->get_record('user', array('id' => $this->properties->requester, 'deleted'=>0), '*', MUST_EXIST);
3066  
3067          $courseconfig = get_config('moodlecourse');
3068  
3069          // Transfer appropriate settings
3070          $data = clone($this->properties);
3071          unset($data->id);
3072          unset($data->reason);
3073          unset($data->requester);
3074  
3075          // Set category
3076          $category = $this->get_category();
3077          $data->category = $category->id;
3078          // Set misc settings
3079          $data->requested = 1;
3080  
3081          // Apply course default settings
3082          $data->format             = $courseconfig->format;
3083          $data->newsitems          = $courseconfig->newsitems;
3084          $data->showgrades         = $courseconfig->showgrades;
3085          $data->showreports        = $courseconfig->showreports;
3086          $data->maxbytes           = $courseconfig->maxbytes;
3087          $data->groupmode          = $courseconfig->groupmode;
3088          $data->groupmodeforce     = $courseconfig->groupmodeforce;
3089          $data->visible            = $courseconfig->visible;
3090          $data->visibleold         = $data->visible;
3091          $data->lang               = $courseconfig->lang;
3092  
3093          $course = create_course($data);
3094          $context = context_course::instance($course->id, MUST_EXIST);
3095  
3096          // add enrol instances
3097          if (!$DB->record_exists('enrol', array('courseid'=>$course->id, 'enrol'=>'manual'))) {
3098              if ($manual = enrol_get_plugin('manual')) {
3099                  $manual->add_default_instance($course);
3100              }
3101          }
3102  
3103          // enrol the requester as teacher if necessary
3104          if (!empty($CFG->creatornewroleid) and !is_viewing($context, $user, 'moodle/role:assign') and !is_enrolled($context, $user, 'moodle/role:assign')) {
3105              enrol_try_internal_enrol($course->id, $user->id, $CFG->creatornewroleid);
3106          }
3107  
3108          $this->delete();
3109  
3110          $a = new stdClass();
3111          $a->name = format_string($course->fullname, true, array('context' => context_course::instance($course->id)));
3112          $a->url = $CFG->wwwroot.'/course/view.php?id=' . $course->id;
3113          $this->notify($user, $USER, 'courserequestapproved', get_string('courseapprovedsubject'), get_string('courseapprovedemail2', 'moodle', $a));
3114  
3115          return $course->id;
3116      }

3166  /**
3167   * Return a list of page types
3168   * @param string $pagetype current page type
3169   * @param context $parentcontext Block's parent context
3170   * @param context $currentcontext Current context of block
3171   * @return array array of page types
3172   */
3173  function course_page_type_list($pagetype, $parentcontext, $currentcontext) {
3174      if ($pagetype === 'course-index' || $pagetype === 'course-index-category') {
3175          // For courses and categories browsing pages (/course/index.php) add option to show on ANY category page
3176          $pagetypes = array('*' => get_string('page-x', 'pagetype'),
3177              'course-index-*' => get_string('page-course-index-x', 'pagetype'),
3178          );
3179      } else if ($currentcontext && (!($coursecontext = $currentcontext->get_course_context(false)) || $coursecontext->instanceid == SITEID)) {
3180          // We know for sure that despite pagetype starts with 'course-' this is not a page in course context (i.e. /course/search.php, etc.)
3181          $pagetypes = array('*' => get_string('page-x', 'pagetype'));
3182      } else {
3183          // Otherwise consider it a page inside a course even if $currentcontext is null
3184          $pagetypes = array('*' => get_string('page-x', 'pagetype'),
3185              'course-*' => get_string('page-course-x', 'pagetype'),
3186              'course-view-*' => get_string('page-course-view-x', 'pagetype')
3187          );
3188      }
3189      return $pagetypes;
3190  }

3192  /**
3193   * Determine whether course ajax should be enabled for the specified course
3194   *
3195   * @param stdClass $course The course to test against
3196   * @return boolean Whether course ajax is enabled or note
3197   */
3198  function course_ajax_enabled($course) {
3199      global $CFG, $PAGE, $SITE;
3200  
3201      // The user must be editing for AJAX to be included
3202      if (!$PAGE->user_is_editing()) {
3203          return false;
3204      }
3205  
3206      // Check that the theme suports
3207      if (!$PAGE->theme->enablecourseajax) {
3208          return false;
3209      }
3210  
3211      // Check that the course format supports ajax functionality
3212      // The site 'format' doesn't have information on course format support
3213      if ($SITE->id !== $course->id) {
3214          $courseformatajaxsupport = course_format_ajax_support($course->format);
3215          if (!$courseformatajaxsupport->capable) {
3216              return false;
3217          }
3218      }
3219  
3220      // All conditions have been met so course ajax should be enabled
3221      return true;
3222  }

3346  /**
3347   * Returns the sorted list of available course formats, filtered by enabled if necessary
3348   *
3349   * @param bool $enabledonly return only formats that are enabled
3350   * @return array array of sorted format names
3351   */
3352  function get_sorted_course_formats($enabledonly = false) {
3353      global $CFG;
3354      $formats = core_component::get_plugin_list('format');
3355  
3356      if (!empty($CFG->format_plugins_sortorder)) {
3357          $order = explode(',', $CFG->format_plugins_sortorder);
3358          $order = array_merge(array_intersect($order, array_keys($formats)),
3359                      array_diff(array_keys($formats), $order));
3360      } else {
3361          $order = array_keys($formats);
3362      }
3363      if (!$enabledonly) {
3364          return $order;
3365      }
3366      $sortedformats = array();
3367      foreach ($order as $formatname) {
3368          if (!get_config('format_'.$formatname, 'disabled')) {
3369              $sortedformats[] = $formatname;
3370          }
3371      }
3372      return $sortedformats;
3373  }

3390  /**

3400   */
3401  function create_module($moduleinfo) {

3500  /**
3501   * Api to duplicate a module.
3502   *
3503   * @param object $course course object.
3504   * @param object $cm course module object to be duplicated.
3505   * @since Moodle 2.8
3506   *
3507   * @throws Exception
3508   * @throws coding_exception
3509   * @throws moodle_exception
3510   * @throws restore_controller_exception
3511   *
3512   * @return cm_info|null cminfo object if we sucessfully duplicated the mod and found the new cm.
3513   */
3514  function duplicate_module($course, $cm) {
3515      global $CFG, $DB, $USER;
3516      require_once($CFG->dirroot . '/backup/util/includes/backup_includes.php');
3517      require_once($CFG->dirroot . '/backup/util/includes/restore_includes.php');
3518      require_once($CFG->libdir . '/filelib.php');
3519  
3520      $a          = new stdClass();
3521      $a->modtype = get_string('modulename', $cm->modname);
3522      $a->modname = format_string($cm->name);
3523  
3524      if (!plugin_supports('mod', $cm->modname, FEATURE_BACKUP_MOODLE2)) {
3525          throw new moodle_exception('duplicatenosupport', 'error', '', $a);
3526      }
3527  
3528      // Backup the activity.
3529  
3530      $bc = new backup_controller(backup::TYPE_1ACTIVITY, $cm->id, backup::FORMAT_MOODLE,
3531              backup::INTERACTIVE_NO, backup::MODE_IMPORT, $USER->id);
3532  
3533      $backupid       = $bc->get_backupid();
3534      $backupbasepath = $bc->get_plan()->get_basepath();
3535  
3536      $bc->execute_plan();
3537  
3538      $bc->destroy();
3539  
3540      // Restore the backup immediately.
3541  
3542      $rc = new restore_controller($backupid, $course->id,
3543              backup::INTERACTIVE_NO, backup::MODE_IMPORT, $USER->id, backup::TARGET_CURRENT_ADDING);
3544  
3545      $cmcontext = context_module::instance($cm->id);
3546      if (!$rc->execute_precheck()) {
3547          $precheckresults = $rc->get_precheck_results();
3548          if (is_array($precheckresults) && !empty($precheckresults['errors'])) {
3549              if (empty($CFG->keeptempdirectoriesonbackup)) {
3550                  fulldelete($backupbasepath);
3551              }
3552          }
3553      }
3554  
3555      $rc->execute_plan();
3556  
3557      // Now a bit hacky part follows - we try to get the cmid of the newly
3558      // restored copy of the module.
3559      $newcmid = null;
3560      $tasks = $rc->get_plan()->get_tasks();
3561      foreach ($tasks as $task) {
3562          if (is_subclass_of($task, 'restore_activity_task')) {
3563              if ($task->get_old_contextid() == $cmcontext->id) {
3564                  $newcmid = $task->get_moduleid();
3565                  break;
3566              }
3567          }
3568      }
3569  
3570      // If we know the cmid of the new course module, let us move it
3571      // right below the original one. otherwise it will stay at the
3572      // end of the section.
3573      if ($newcmid) {
3574          $info = get_fast_modinfo($course);
3575          $newcm = $info->get_cm($newcmid);
3576          $section = $DB->get_record('course_sections', array('id' => $cm->section, 'course' => $cm->course));
3577          moveto_module($newcm, $section, $cm);
3578          moveto_module($cm, $section, $newcm);
3579  
3580          // Trigger course module created event. We can trigger the event only if we know the newcmid.
3581          $event = \core\event\course_module_created::create_from_cm($newcm);
3582          $event->trigger();
3583      }
3584      rebuild_course_cache($cm->course);
3585  
3586      $rc->destroy();
3587  
3588      if (empty($CFG->keeptempdirectoriesonbackup)) {
3589          fulldelete($backupbasepath);
3590      }
3591  
3592      return isset($newcm) ? $newcm : null;
3593  }

3595  /**
3596   * Compare two objects to find out their correct order based on timestamp (to be used by usort).
3597   * Sorts by descending order of time.
3598   *
3599   * @param stdClass $a First object
3600   * @param stdClass $b Second object
3601   * @return int 0,1,-1 representing the order
3602   */
3603  function compare_activities_by_time_desc($a, $b) {
3604      // Make sure the activities actually have a timestamp property.
3605      if ((!property_exists($a, 'timestamp')) && (!property_exists($b, 'timestamp'))) {
3606          return 0;
3607      }
3608      // We treat instances without timestamp as if they have a timestamp of 0.
3609      if ((!property_exists($a, 'timestamp')) && (property_exists($b,'timestamp'))) {
3610          return 1;
3611      }
3612      if ((property_exists($a, 'timestamp')) && (!property_exists($b, 'timestamp'))) {
3613          return -1;
3614      }
3615      if ($a->timestamp == $b->timestamp) {
3616          return 0;
3617      }
3618      return ($a->timestamp > $b->timestamp) ? -1 : 1;
3619  }

3663  /**
3664   * Changes the course sortorder by one, moving it up or down one in respect to sort order.
3665   *
3666   * @param stdClass|course_in_list $course
3667   * @param bool $up If set to true the course will be moved up one. Otherwise down one.
3668   * @return bool
3669   */
3670  function course_change_sortorder_by_one($course, $up) {
3671      global $DB;
3672      $params = array($course->sortorder, $course->category);
3673      if ($up) {
3674          $select = 'sortorder < ? AND category = ?';
3675          $sort = 'sortorder DESC';
3676      } else {
3677          $select = 'sortorder > ? AND category = ?';
3678          $sort = 'sortorder ASC';
3679      }
3680      fix_course_sortorder();
3681      $swapcourse = $DB->get_records_select('course', $select, $params, $sort, '*', 0, 1);
3682      if ($swapcourse) {
3683          $swapcourse = reset($swapcourse);
3684          $DB->set_field('course', 'sortorder', $swapcourse->sortorder, array('id' => $course->id));
3685          $DB->set_field('course', 'sortorder', $course->sortorder, array('id' => $swapcourse->id));
3686          // Finally reorder courses.
3687          fix_course_sortorder();
3688          cache_helper::purge_by_event('changesincourse');
3689          return true;
3690      }
3691      return false;
3692  }

3694  /**
3695   * Changes the sort order of courses in a category so that the first course appears after the second.
3696   *
3697   * @param int|stdClass $courseorid The course to focus on.
3698   * @param int $moveaftercourseid The course to shifter after or 0 if you want it to be the first course in the category.
3699   * @return bool
3700   */
3701  function course_change_sortorder_after_course($courseorid, $moveaftercourseid) {
3702      global $DB;
3703  
3704      if (!is_object($courseorid)) {
3705          $course = get_course($courseorid);
3706      } else {
3707          $course = $courseorid;
3708      }
3709  
3710      if ((int)$moveaftercourseid === 0) {
3711          // We've moving the course to the start of the queue.
3712          $sql = 'SELECT sortorder
3713                        FROM {course}
3714                       WHERE category = :categoryid
3715                    ORDER BY sortorder';
3716          $params = array(
3717              'categoryid' => $course->category
3718          );
3719          $sortorder = $DB->get_field_sql($sql, $params, IGNORE_MULTIPLE);
3720  
3721          $sql = 'UPDATE {course}
3722                     SET sortorder = sortorder + 1
3723                   WHERE category = :categoryid
3724                     AND id <> :id';
3725          $params = array(
3726              'categoryid' => $course->category,
3727              'id' => $course->id,
3728          );
3729          $DB->execute($sql, $params);
3730          $DB->set_field('course', 'sortorder', $sortorder, array('id' => $course->id));
3731      } else if ($course->id === $moveaftercourseid) {
3732          // They're the same - moronic.
3733          debugging("Invalid move after course given.", DEBUG_DEVELOPER);
3734          return false;
3735      } else {
3736          // Moving this course after the given course. It could be before it could be after.
3737          $moveaftercourse = get_course($moveaftercourseid);
3738          if ($course->category !== $moveaftercourse->category) {
3739              debugging("Cannot re-order courses. The given courses do not belong to the same category.", DEBUG_DEVELOPER);
3740              return false;
3741          }
3742          // Increment all courses in the same category that are ordered after the moveafter course.
3743          // This makes a space for the course we're moving.
3744          $sql = 'UPDATE {course}
3745                         SET sortorder = sortorder + 1
3746                       WHERE category = :categoryid
3747                         AND sortorder > :sortorder';
3748          $params = array(
3749              'categoryid' => $moveaftercourse->category,
3750              'sortorder' => $moveaftercourse->sortorder
3751          );
3752          $DB->execute($sql, $params);
3753          $DB->set_field('course', 'sortorder', $moveaftercourse->sortorder + 1, array('id' => $course->id));
3754      }
3755      fix_course_sortorder();
3756      cache_helper::purge_by_event('changesincourse');
3757      return true;
3758  }
